# Pine Script v6 — Zed Rules
# Author: Ugur Pala · mail@ugurpala.com · github.com/trugurpala/pinescriptv6
# TR: Zed editörü için Pine Script v6 kural dosyası
# EN: Pine Script v6 rules for Zed editor

## Protocol

Before writing any Pine Script v6 code:
1. Read LESSONS_LEARNED.md — known errors and fixes
2. Use LLM_MANIFEST.md to find the correct reference file
3. Read that file, then write the code
4. On error: solve it + append to LESSONS_LEARNED.md

## Non-Negotiable Rules

1. //@version=6 — first line of EVERY script
2. ta.* functions — never reimplement manually
3. input.int(), input.float() etc — never bare input()
4. request.security() — never security()
5. indicator() — never study()

## Reference Map

| Need | File |
|------|------|
| Indicators (RSI, EMA, MACD, ATR) | reference/functions/ta.md |
| Strategies | reference/functions/strategy.md |
| Drawings (plot, line, label, table) | reference/functions/drawing.md |
| MTF (request.security) | reference/functions/request.md |
| Arrays, maps, matrices | reference/functions/collections.md |
| Math, string, input, alert | reference/functions/general.md |
| Errors | concepts/common_errors.md |
| **Always first** | LESSONS_LEARNED.md |

## Checklist

- [ ] LESSONS_LEARNED.md read
- [ ] //@version=6 present
- [ ] No v5 syntax
- [ ] Function signatures verified against reference
- [ ] var/varip used correctly
